e story through significant moments in California history, including the birth of the mestizo in Mexico, destruction of Indian lifeways under the mission system, violence toward Mexicanos during the Gold Rush, Chicano farm life in the early twentieth century, the Chicano Movement of the 1960s, Chicano-Latino activism in San Francisco in the 1970s, and the current rebirth of Chicano-Indio culture. Rejecting the notion that history is always written by the victors, and refusing to be one of the vanquished, he declares, "This is my California history, my memories, richly subjective and atavistic."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Okt 2021) 0aAztecsxFirst contact with EuropeanszCaliforniaxHistory. 0aMexican American familieszCaliforniaxHistory. 0aMexican AmericanszCaliforniavBiography. 0aMexican AmericanszCaliforniaxHistory. 0aMexican AmericanszCaliforniazSan FranciscovBiography. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292796379423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292796379/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK